Could you explain in what case we will have 2 consecutive limits, and the upper limit contains valid offset?
In my understanding, limit contains valid offset if and only if its child is a sort node.

>  In my understanding, limit contains valid offset if and only if its child is a sort node.

Yes, a valid plan should not have consecutive limits that both have valid offset but on sort between them. This is to restrict the condition that the rule can apply. We could have a dedicated check logic to check a limit plan with a valid offset but its child is not a sort node.
